AB  - Renewable energy sources offer a promising method of environmentally friendly and sustainable electricity generation in remote areas. Among various renewable energy sources, solar power is usable everywhere as long as there is solar radiation. It is particularly useful for isolated areas where there is no access to any other source of electricity. However, the inherent uncertainty of solar radiation and climate changes may result in a high initial investment cost that could make this type of energy system economically infeasible. To obtain a PV-battery system at a reasonable investment cost, a home-backup diesel generator is assumed to be available. We develop a scenario-based optimization model to determine the capacity of residential off-grid PV-battery systems that consider solar radiation uncertainty and hourly energy consumption patterns. The optimization model determines the PV-battery capacities to supply the energy demanded at each period by minimizing the annual equivalent investment cost and the fuel cost of using the diesel generator. The impact of scenarios on the model results is evaluated by changing the number of scenarios. © 2022
