AB  - This paper presents a PV–powered water pumping system for rural or remote areas an alternate to grid powered water pump system. The three-phase induction motor could be a prevailing solution for the existing dc motor water pumping system since the cost of the system is high. The controller for a photovoltaic powered induction motor water pumping system without using any battery or any chemical charge/storage element is presented. Proposed system has a modified Two-Inductor Boost Converter (TIBC), analog circuit based MPPT, and a full-bridge three-phase Voltage Source Inverter (VSI) connected to induction motor and pump. The modified TIBC topology has features like high voltage gain, low input current ripple, with further improvement on the use of maximum power point technique (MPPT) algorithm for the efficient utilization of available solar power. The system also achieves a more competent, consistent, maintenance-free and an low-priced solution for ac motors. An algorithmic rule supporting power-seeking controller adjusts the motor speed position to realize the MPPT operation of the photovoltaic array. As a result, the system may be a promising key to be employed in isolated locations, to deliver water in remote/isolated areas. © 2018, Institute of Advanced Scientific Research, Inc. All rights reserved.
